<title type="html"><![CDATA[NES and the Internet]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=848&amp;p=7595#p7595"><![CDATA[
Is it possible to do multiplayer NES gaming?  That requires two way communication.  One person would act as the host, the other(s) the clients, but only the host must have a copy of the game.  The host's computer will control the flow of the gameplay and must send graphics and sound information to each client NES.  In turn, each client NES must send controller data to the host NES.  The client NESs must be entirely passive, data must be written to them but they cannot send data.  That is essentially what would be required to make existing multiplayer games to work.  I believe that modems for the SNES and Genesis exist that must do this, so it is not entirely unfeasible.  It may require game-specific setting though.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=58">Great Hierophant</a> — Wed Dec 21, 2005 2:51 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
